  "author_association": "NONE",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "As a developer / user I want to be able to download a Flatpak or .deb version of Status Desktop, so I don't need to hunt for an AppImage every single time I want to use the app.\r\n\r\n### Problems with AppImage:\r\n* Cannot search for Status in the global search\r\n* AppImage cannot actually be installed, which means users can't pin Status to the dock, or interact with it like a normal app\r\n* They are resource restricted and containerized, which means there's stability issues for long-term usage\r\n* Updates don't apply properly, and I must often delete the database and reinstall it before opening the AppImage\r\n\r\nFlatpak, .deb, and snap packages all solve these four major problems on Linux",
